   "source": [
    "### NCHS dataset\n",
    "\n",
    "1. The data is collected through the National College Health Assessment, which is a large-scale survey conducted at colleges and universities across the United States of America, aiming to collect data on the health of college students. The data includes student responses to the online survey, which include standardized measures of mental health, including psychological distress, loneliness, suicide risk screening, wellbeing, resilience, campus belonging, health behaviors such as physical activity, BMI, food security, and service utilization.\n",
    "   \n",
    "2. Important metrics: \n",
    "\n",
    "respondent_id: unique ID for each survey respondent\n",
    "\n",
    "sex_group_RSEX: sex/gender group category\n",
    "\n",
    "self_rated_health: self-rated overall health (e.g., excellent → poor)\n",
    "\n",
    "belonging_item: sense of belonging (Likert; higher = more belonging)\n",
    "\n",
    "wellbeing_priority_item: agreement that wellbeing is a campus priority (Likert)\n",
    "\n",
    "open_discussion_item: agreement that wellbeing/mental health can be discussed openly (Likert)\n",
    "\n",
    "look_out_for_each_other_item: agreement that people on campus look out for each other (Likert)\n",
    "\n",
    "aerobic_guideline_met: meets aerobic activity guideline (0/1)\n",
    "\n",
    "strength_guideline_met: meets strength-training guideline (0/1)\n",
    "\n",
    "active_adult_met: meets overall active adult criteria (0/1)\n",
    "\n",
    "food_security_level: food security category (more insecure = worse)\n",
    "\n",
    "any_food_insecurity: any food insecurity indicator (0/1)\n",
    "\n",
    "medical_visit_12mo: had a medical visit in past 12 months (0/1)\n",
    "\n",
    "mh_services_12mo: used mental health services in past 12 months (0/1)\n",
    "\n",
    "k6_distress_score: K6 psychological distress score (0–24; higher = more distress)\n",
    "\n",
