    "#### Section 2 of EDA - Distribution of Student Mental Health Indicators \n",
    "\n",
    "After cleaning the dataset, we examined the distributions of the key mental health indicators: K6 distress score, ULS-3 loneliness score, psychological well-being score, and resilience score. Histograms were used to visualize how these variables are distributed across the 4,753 respondents in the cleaned dataset.\n",
    "\n",
    "The plots show that distress and loneliness scores vary across students, with most respondents reporting lower or moderate values and fewer students reporting very high levels. Psychological well-being and resilience scores appear more concentrated around moderate to higher values.\n",
    "\n",
    "Overall, these distributions suggest that student mental health outcomes vary widely across individuals, providing a useful basis for further analysis comparing mental well-being across institutions.\n"
   ]
